  "text": "$&S-labelled Mycβ and Mycβ C\"!*,\"\"%S were produced by in itro transcription and translation using a TnT kit (Promega) with T7 polymerase according to the manufacturer's instructions. For studies on protein translation through time, 5 µl aliquots of $&S-labelled Mycβ and Mycβ C\"!*,\"\"%S were removed every 15 min until the completion of the 90 min reaction. GST-fusion proteins encoding full-length CK2αh or GST alone were expressed in bacteria and purified using glutathione-agarose as described previously [CITATION_1] . The purified fusion proteins were then coupled to Affi-Gel 10 (Bio-Rad) at a concentration of 4 mg\\ml according to the manufacturer's instructions. Following in itro transcription and translation, GST-pulldowns were performed by diluting the TnT reactions with 50 µl RIPA buffer (50 mM Tris, pH 8.0, 150 mM NaCl, 1 % Nonidet P40, 0.5 % deoxycholate and 0.1 % SDS) and adding 10 µl of Affi-Gel 10 GST or GST-αh beads. Incubation was at 4 mC for 1 h with rocking. The AffiGel beads were collected by centrifugation, the supernatant was removed and the beads were washed four times with 100 µl RIPA buffer. Proteins bound to the Affi-Gel beads were eluted by the addition of 2i Laemmli sample buffer and were subjected to SDS\\PAGE on a 12 % gel. After drying, the radiolabelled proteins were revealed using a PhosphorImager.",
